       for the job CWD:

       bsub -cwd "/scratch/jobcwd/%U/%J_%I" myjob

       The system creates submission_dir/user1/<jobid>_0/ for the job's
       CWD with the following command:

       bsub -cwd "%U/%J_%I" myprog

       If the cluster wide CWD was defined and there is no default ap‐
       plication profile CWD defined:

       [1mDEFAULT_JOB_CWD =/scratch/jobcwd/ %U/%J_%I[0m

       then the system creates: /scratch/jobcwd/user1/<jobid>_0/ for the
       job's CWD.

