                                      [1m-K[0m

       Submits a job and waits for the job to complete. Sends job status
       messages to the terminal.

[1mCategories[0m
       notify, properties

[1mSynopsis[0m
       [1mbsub -K[0m

[1mConflicting options[0m
       Do not use with the following options: -I, -Ip, -IS, -ISp, -ISs,
       -Is, -IX.

[1mDescription[0m
       Sends the message "Waiting for dispatch" to the terminal when you
       submit the job. Sends the message "Job is finished" to the termi‐
       nal when the job is done (if [1mLSB_SUBK_SHOW_JOBID [22mis enabled in
       the lsf.conf file or as an environment variable, also displays
       the job ID when the job is done).

       If [1mLSB_SUBK_SHOW_EXEC_HOST [22mis enabled in lsf.conf, also sends the
       message "Starting on [4mexecution_host[24m" when the job starts running
       on the execution host.

       You are not able to submit another job until the job is com‐
       pleted. This is useful when completion of the job is required to
       proceed, such as a job script. If the job needs to be rerun due
       to transient failures, bsub returns after the job finishes suc‐
       cessfully. bsub exits with the same exit code as the job so that
       job scripts can take appropriate actions based on the exit codes.
       bsub exits with value 126 if the job was terminated while pend‐
       ing.

