                                      [1m-Zs[0m

       Spools a job command file to the directory specified by the
       [1mJOB_SPOOL_DIR [22mparameter in lsb.params, and uses the spooled file
       as the command file for the job.

[1mCategories[0m
       properties, script

[1mSynopsis[0m
       [1mbsub -Zs[0m

[1mDescription[0m
       By default, the command file is spooled to LSB_SHAREDIR/[4mclus‐[0m
       [4mter_name[24m/lsf_cmddir. If the lsf_cmddir directory does not exist,
       LSF creates it before spooling the file. LSF removes the spooled
       file when the job completes.

       If [1mJOB_SPOOL_DIR [22mis specified, the -Zs option spools the command
       file to the specified directory and uses the spooled file as the
       input file for the job.

       [1mJOB_SPOOL_DIR [22mcan be any valid path up to a maximum length up to
