       [1mJOB_SPOOL_DIR [22mmust be readable and writable by the job submission
       user, and it must be shared by the management host and the sub‐
       mission host. If the specified directory is not accessible or
       does not exist, bsub -Zs cannot write to the default directory
       LSB_SHAREDIR/[4mcluster_name[24m/lsf_cmddir and the job fails.

       The -Zs option is not supported for embedded job commands because
       LSF is unable to determine the first command to be spooled in an
